'''Vladeta Jerotić''' (Владета Јеротић), [[Academician]], [[Prof]]. [[Dr]]., is a [[Serbs|Serbian]] [[writer]] and [[psychiatrist]]. He was born on [[August 2]], [[1924]] in [[Belgrade]], in the [[Kingdom of Serbs, Croats and Slovenes]]. 

He represents of the most influetial figures in Serbian but also regional [[culture]], in the field of [[psychology]], [[psychoterapy]], [[psychiatry]], [[theology]] and [[literature]]. With more than 200 books, articles and essays, he is one of the most fruitfull contemporary writers in Serbian language. 

In 2000, he was elected as a member of [[Serbian Academy of Sciences and Arts]] in the Department of Language and Literature.

He was also a [[full professor]] of the [[Faculty of Theology]], [[University of Belgrade]], teaching the pastorial psychology. 

